##########
# README #
##########

[ Description ]
gtk-splitter can split files into smaller pieces and combine them back together. It can also generate
a DOS batch file so that the split files can be combined on DOS/Windows systems. gtk-splitter is good
for working around file limitations with floppy disks, email attachments, etc.

[ Submitting bugs and feature requests ]
E-mail me at techgunter@yahoo.com

[ Detailed install instructions ]
SEE INSTALL

[ Installing from CVS ]

-Required packages:
 +autoconf
 +automake
 +make
 +C compiler
 +gtk+
 +gtk+-devel

-Procedure:
 + >./autogen.sh
 + >./configure
 + >make
 + >make install (as root)

[ Installing from source package ]

-Required packages:
 +make
 +C compiler
 +gtk+
 +gtk+-devel

-Procedure:
 + >tar -xzvf gtk-splitter-VERSION.tar.gz
 + >cd gtk-splitter-VERSION
 + >./configure
 + >make
 + >make install (as root)

[ Building an RPM package from CVS ]

-Required packages:
 +autoconf
 +automake
 +make
 +C compiler
 +gtk+
 +gtk+-devel
 +rpm

-Procedure:
 + >./autogen.sh
 + >./build_rpm.sh

[ Building an RPM package from source ]

-Required packages:
 +make
 +C compiler
 +gtk+
 +gtk+-devel
 +rpm

-Procedure:
 + >./build_rpm.sh

[ Installing the RPM package ]

-Required packages:
 +gtk+
 +rpm

-Procedure:
 + >rpm -ivh gtk-splitter-VERSION.i386.rpm (as root)
 + >rpm -ivh gtk-splitter-VERSION.src.rpm (as root; optional)
